  "text": "GCC's optimization pass registration and execution follows a sophisticated pipeline architecture defined across six key files in github.com/sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333 (a version-pinned mirror of gcc-mirror/gcc):\n\n**Pass Definition and Ordering (gcc/passes.def:1-100)**\nThe master list of all optimization passes is defined in gcc/passes.def using declarative macros. This file uses INSERT_PASSES_AFTER and NEXT_PASS macros to specify the hierarchical structure and ordering of passes. For example, it defines pass groups like 'all_lowering_passes', 'all_small_ipa_passes', 'all_regular_ipa_passes', 'all_late_ipa_passes', and 'all_passes'. The file is processed by an AWK script to generate instance-specific definitions.\n\n**Pass Instance Generation (gcc/gen-pass-instances.awk:1-60)**\nThe gen-pass-instances.awk script automatically generates pass-instances.def from passes.def by counting pass instances and adding numbering (e.g., converting 'NEXT_PASS (pass_copy_prop);' to 'NEXT_PASS (pass_copy_prop, 1);' through 'NEXT_PASS (pass_copy_prop, 8);'). This enables proper handling of passes that have multiple instances in the pipeline.\n\n**Pass Manager Implementation (gcc/passes.cc:1-150, 1600-1750)**\nThe passes.cc file implements the core pass manager functionality. Key methods include:\n- opt_pass::clone() (line 87-91): Provides default implementation with error handling for cloneable passes\n- opt_pass::gate() (line 100-104): Default gate implementation returning true\n- opt_pass::execute() (line 106-110): Default execute returning 0\n- pass_manager::execute_early_local_passes() (line 123-127): Executes early SSA and local optimization passes\n- pass_manager::execute_pass_mode_switching() (line 129-133): Executes mode-switching pass\n\nThe pass manager constructor uses NEXT_PASS macros (defined at lines 1619-1630) to instantiate and wire up the pass tree by calling make_pass_* factory functions for each pass.\n\n**Pass Manager Structure (gcc/pass_manager.h:1-100)**\nThe pass_manager class (lines 47-51) maintains the pass tree hierarchy with public members:\n- opt_pass *all_passes, *all_small_ipa_passes, *all_lowering_passes, *all_regular_ipa_passes, *all_late_ipa_passes: Root nodes for each pass group\n- opt_pass **passes_by_id: Array mapping static pass IDs to passes\n- GCC_PASS_LISTS macro (lines 28-33): Defines the five pass list categories used throughout compilation\n\n**Pass Base Classes and Interface (gcc/tree-pass.h:1-250)**\nThe tree-pass.h header defines the optimization pass hierarchy:\n- pass_data struct (lines 40-64): Metadata containing pass type, name, required/provided/destroyed properties, todo flags\n- opt_pass class (lines 73-113): Abstract base class with virtual methods gate() (line 90) and execute() (line 96), plus sub and next pointers for the pass tree structure\n- gimple_opt_pass (lines 116-123): Specialized base for tree-SSA/GIMPLE passes\n- rtl_opt_pass (lines 126-133): Specialized base for RTL generation and optimization passes\n- ipa_opt_pass_d (lines 141-193): IPA pass base with hooks for summary generation, writing/reading, and transformations\n- simple_ipa_opt_pass (lines 197-204): Lightweight IPA pass base with single execute hook\nProperty macros (lines 206-232) like PROP_cfg, PROP_ssa, PROP_rtl define pass requirements and guarantees. Todo flags (lines 239-250) specify operations to perform after pass completion.\n\n**Concrete DCE Pass Implementation (gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc:2030-2150)**\nThe tree-ssa-dce.cc file exemplifies a complete GIMPLE pass implementation:\n- pass_data_dce (lines 2038-2049): Metadata declaring regular DCE as GIMPLE_PASS requiring PROP_cfg and PROP_ssa\n- pass_data_cd_dce (lines 2108-2119): Metadata for control-dependent DCE variant (\"cddce\")\n- pass_dce_base (lines 2051-2079): Abstract base class providing:\n  - gate() override checking flag_tree_dce (line 2055)\n  - set_pass_param() for configurable options (lines 2056-2063)\n  - execute_dce() template method (lines 2069-2074) calling perform_tree_ssa_dce()\n- pass_dce (lines 2082-2096): Concrete regular DCE pass calling execute_dce with aggressive=false\n- pass_cd_dce (lines 2121-2135): Concrete control-dependent DCE pass calling execute_dce with aggressive=(optimize>=2)\n- make_pass_dce() (lines 2100-2104) and make_pass_cd_dce() (lines 2139-2143): Factory functions creating pass instances\n- perform_tree_ssa_dce(): Core algorithm iterating the three phases: marking necessary statements, propagating necessity, and removing dead statements\n\n**Execution Chain:**\n1. Compiler invokes pass_manager constructor from passes.cc with #include \"pass-instances.def\"\n2. NEXT_PASS macros (line 1619) call make_pass_cd_dce() to instantiate pass_cd_dce objects\n3. Each pass_cd_dce instance inherits from gimple_opt_pass and implements execute() (line 2130)\n4. During compilation, the pass manager traverses the opt_pass tree executing gate() checks followed by execute() calls\n5. perform_tree_ssa_dce() is invoked from pass_cd_dce::execute() which implements the actual dead code elimination algorithm\n6. Results from pass execution (todo flags) are applied to update compiler state (SSA, control flow graphs, etc.)\n\nThis architecture provides a flexible, extensible system where new passes can be added by defining pass_data metadata, implementing a pass class inheriting from an appropriate base (gimple_opt_pass, rtl_opt_pass, etc.), providing a make_pass_* factory function, and registering in passes.def—no changes to the core pass manager code required."
}

